      <title>Understanding Hashing</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/hashing/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 31 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/hashing/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;understanding-hashing&#34;&gt;Understanding Hashing&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hashing is one of the most important techniques in computer science.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;why-do-we-need-hashing&#34;&gt;Why do we need Hashing?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Many applications require fast search operations:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dictionary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Database Index&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Symbol Table&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;File System Index&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-is-a-hash-table&#34;&gt;What is a Hash Table?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A hash table stores data using a hash function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;h(k) = k mod m&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;collision&#34;&gt;Collision&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A collision occurs when two keys map to the same slot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;15 → 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;25 → 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;chaining&#34;&gt;Chaining&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Store colliding elements in a linked list.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
